WEBVTT

00:03.521 --> 00:07.346
<i>[shower running]
[music]</i>

00:14.482 --> 00:17.233
[grunting]

00:19.000 --> 00:25.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:38.039 --> 00:40.706
What the fuck do you want?

00:40.791 --> 00:41.957
<i>[switchblade clicks]</i>

00:42.093 --> 00:43.292
[gasps]

00:44.879 --> 00:47.463
[clicking]

00:50.134 --> 00:52.551
<i>[theme music playing]</i>

01:51.584 --> 01:54.621
4x07 - "Truths Other
Than the Ones You Tell Yourself"

02:00.840 --> 02:03.903
<i><font color="red"> sync & correction by f1nc0
~ Addic7ed.com ~ </font></i>

02:05.209 --> 02:08.009
<i>Hubbard: You want to tell
me how you got those bruises?</i>

02:10.715 --> 02:12.214
Not really.

02:12.350 --> 02:15.267
<i>You afraid if you do, you
won't get your kids back?</i>

02:17.555 --> 02:21.774
I'm starting to wonder if I should
be more afraid of getting them back.

02:24.195 --> 02:26.645
I don't deserve to be their mother.

02:28.232 --> 02:31.784
Maybe I don't deserve anything
more than exactly what I got.

02:35.823 --> 02:38.574
I'm gonna give you a free pass.

02:38.659 --> 02:42.745
Nothing you say now will affect
my custody recommendation.

02:42.830 --> 02:45.748
<i>You have my word.
This is off the record.</i>

02:45.883 --> 02:47.383
Why would you do that?

02:47.468 --> 02:50.135
Because believe it or not,
I'm trying to help you...

02:51.338 --> 02:53.222
and I can't without the truth.

03:02.500 --> 03:04.483
I put her in danger again.

03:04.602 --> 03:07.152
<i>Who, Deva?
She was home?</i>

03:07.271 --> 03:10.823
- What happened?
- They came for me.

03:10.941 --> 03:13.242
Who came for you, Carrie?

03:13.327 --> 03:16.028
You want the truth?

03:17.198 --> 03:19.031
I'm a liar.

03:19.116 --> 03:22.284
I lied to my family.
I lied to my husband.

03:22.420 --> 03:25.838
Gordon, he never lied.

03:27.091 --> 03:30.259
And his truth is the
only one I have left.

03:32.012 --> 03:36.131
He dedicated his whole life
to fighting corruption in this town.

03:36.217 --> 03:39.885
And you feel you have to see it through
because he died saving you.

03:39.970 --> 03:41.770
- It's not so simple.
- Then help me.

03:41.856 --> 03:44.640
Help me out with it.
Help me understand, Carrie.

03:44.725 --> 03:48.811
What's the truth?
Carrie, help me...

03:48.896 --> 03:51.613
That I never stopped
loving somebody else!

03:58.372 --> 04:03.792
- I know, I have to stop this fighting.
- No.

04:03.878 --> 04:08.078
You have to finish what you started.
[music]

04:09.383 --> 04:11.300
What kind of shrink are you?

04:11.385 --> 04:13.335
<i>This is not the shrink talking.</i>

04:13.471 --> 04:15.170
This is the father in me.

04:15.256 --> 04:17.839
And I know that until
you make peace with this,

04:17.925 --> 04:21.343
you can't be the parent
that your children need.

04:21.428 --> 04:23.846
So go finish it.

04:36.823 --> 04:40.998
[music]

04:43.200 --> 04:47.703
[man wheezing, coughing]

04:51.509 --> 04:52.875
Where's my drugs?

04:53.010 --> 04:56.545
- They took everything.
- Who did?

04:56.680 --> 04:58.881
<i>I... I don't...</i>

04:58.966 --> 05:01.934
[groans]

05:08.275 --> 05:09.775
<i>[groans]</i>

05:09.894 --> 05:13.529
You let Calvin Bunker
take my drugs? Huh?

05:13.614 --> 05:17.900
You let Bunker take my drugs?
[grunting]

05:22.289 --> 05:24.239
<i>Dawson: Hey, it's Veronica.</i>

05:24.375 --> 05:27.910
<i>You disappeared on me this morning.</i>

05:27.995 --> 05:31.663
<i>But anyway, I tracked down
our statutory rape victim.</i>

05:31.749 --> 05:35.801
<i>She said all the right things,
but my bullshit meter is ringing.</i>

05:35.920 --> 05:40.255
<i>Anyway, I'm going back
to the hotel, so call me</i>

05:40.341 --> 05:42.841
<i>and I can fill you in on the...</i>

05:45.145 --> 05:47.679
<i>Brock: Okay, hotel
surveillance shows Dawson</i>

05:47.765 --> 05:50.119
leaving the property
a little before noon yesterday.

05:50.154 --> 05:52.851
I've got every available
deputy out searching for her.

05:52.937 --> 05:55.404
FBI is mobilizing a task force.

05:56.607 --> 06:00.943
She won't live that long.
We have to find her now.

06:01.078 --> 06:02.494
<i>How?</i>

06:02.613 --> 06:05.948
Hood, I have been hunting for
this son of a bitch for months

06:06.083 --> 06:09.429
and all I got is dead ends.
[sighs]

06:10.621 --> 06:14.373
What about the girl?
The one that burned herself.

06:14.458 --> 06:16.124
<i>Gail Westcott.</i>

06:16.210 --> 06:19.127
We searched her apartment three times.

06:19.213 --> 06:21.630
We can't find a single
connection to Bode.

06:23.350 --> 06:26.468
I did request an expedited
subpoena for her cell phone records,

06:26.604 --> 06:29.054
- but that's still gonna take a few days.
- You still got the phone?

06:29.139 --> 06:32.524
- Well, yeah, I mean, what's left of it.
- Let's go.

06:32.643 --> 06:36.028
<i>[music playing]
[sighs]</i>

06:42.820 --> 06:46.655
- I've seen that look before.
- [sighs] I need your help.

06:46.740 --> 06:50.042
Some things never change, do they?

06:50.160 --> 06:53.578
- Just like old times.
- Well, you're the expert on old.

06:53.664 --> 06:57.215
- Wait a minute. I know you.
- Excuse me?

06:57.334 --> 06:58.717
You and I were in a gunfight together

06:58.836 --> 07:01.169
with the Ukrainian
gangsters at the metalworks.

07:01.305 --> 07:03.839
Correction, I was in a gunfight.

07:03.924 --> 07:07.092
You were lying on the floor crying
about your motherfucking leg.

07:07.177 --> 07:09.177
What's in the bag?

07:09.313 --> 07:12.648
Cell phone. I need the call history.

07:13.600 --> 07:15.734
Last few days.

07:21.992 --> 07:25.027
Look, I'm afraid there's not
much to work with there...

07:25.112 --> 07:27.029
Maybe for your police techs.

07:27.164 --> 07:29.698
This got something to
do with the Bowman girl?

07:29.833 --> 07:31.166
Yeah.

07:31.251 --> 07:34.369
Give me 15 minutes.
Sugar, where's my computer?

07:34.455 --> 07:39.340
- Exactly where you left it.
- Well, it ain't gonna fetch itself.

07:53.357 --> 07:56.858
[breathing heavily]

08:11.293 --> 08:13.293
[music]

08:13.294 --> 08:15.494
Fuck!

08:21.752 --> 08:24.386
[panting]

09:02.623 --> 09:04.959
[rattling]

09:15.556 --> 09:17.522
[groans]

09:25.983 --> 09:27.816
[computer chirps]
I'm in.

09:27.951 --> 09:30.988
The heat scrambled most of the
internal memory, but there was

09:30.989 --> 09:34.122
still enough raw data for me to
recover the ESN and hack the log.

09:34.208 --> 09:36.992
[chuckles] I have no
idea what you're saying,

09:37.077 --> 09:39.795
but I sure as hell
missed hearing you say it.

09:39.880 --> 09:42.664
What time did that girl
set herself on fire?

09:42.749 --> 09:45.801
- 7:00 A.M.
- She make any calls that morning?

09:45.886 --> 09:48.753
Five in the two hours
before she grilled herself.

09:48.839 --> 09:51.840
- All to the same number.
- Bode.

09:51.925 --> 09:53.675
Give me the number.
I'll have my people do a trace.

09:53.811 --> 09:56.394
I already traced it.
You best keep up, cop.

09:56.513 --> 09:58.597
Belongs to a Kim Newton.
You know her?

09:58.682 --> 10:00.732
No, but I'm guessing
she's connected to Bode.

10:00.851 --> 10:02.851
Address.

10:03.854 --> 10:05.320
Thanks.

10:09.500 --> 10:12.899
[music]

10:14.081 --> 10:16.114
<i>[door opens]</i>

10:24.374 --> 10:27.459
Who the fuck let you in here?

10:30.514 --> 10:32.931
I'm looking for Calvin.

10:33.050 --> 10:35.517
You must also be looking
to get your ass kicked.

10:35.602 --> 10:39.837
Mr. Bunker took something
that didn't belong to him.

10:41.108 --> 10:43.441
My employer would like it back.

10:43.560 --> 10:46.394
Yeah?
Well, you can tell Proctor

10:46.480 --> 10:48.530
<i>to go fuck himself.</i>

10:48.615 --> 10:53.735
- We're putting him out of business.
- Oh.

11:03.580 --> 11:05.213
I see.

11:11.221 --> 11:13.722
<i>- Man: Easy!
- Man #2: You, you!</i>

11:13.807 --> 11:15.724
<i>[men shouting]
[blows landing]</i>

11:15.809 --> 11:19.227
<i>[men screaming]
[squelching]</i>

11:24.184 --> 11:26.851
<i>[screaming stops]
[body thuds]</i>

11:30.490 --> 11:33.575
[breathing heavily]

11:49.960 --> 11:52.844
You're an FBI agent.

11:55.632 --> 12:01.019
Yeah.
And you're a serial killer.

12:01.238 --> 12:07.234
I don't kill them
because I like to, you know.

12:09.813 --> 12:11.396
<i>I know.</i>

12:11.481 --> 12:16.034
- You kill them because you're insane.
- It's all relative, right?

12:16.153 --> 12:21.489
Not really, no.
You think Satan speaks to you.

12:21.575 --> 12:25.577
There is no Satan.
Ergo, you're insane.

12:25.662 --> 12:28.630
You're not afraid of me, are you?

12:28.715 --> 12:31.166
Oh, don't take it personally.

12:31.301 --> 12:34.970
I've just seen behind the
curtain one too many times.

12:35.055 --> 12:40.675
- The curtain?
- Yeah, you know, like "The Wizard of Oz."

12:40.811 --> 12:46.514
Turns out the big powerful wizard
is just smoke and mirrors,

12:46.650 --> 12:50.735
a delusional old fart
with a few magic tricks.

12:52.439 --> 12:54.856
You know what I think?

12:54.941 --> 12:57.192
<i>What's that?</i>

12:57.327 --> 12:59.444
I think you've taken down enough wizards

12:59.529 --> 13:03.698
to wonder if maybe they know
something that you don't.

13:03.834 --> 13:08.870
<i>That maybe there are truths
other than the ones you tell yourself.</i>

13:09.006 --> 13:14.376
And those truths
have fucked you up so badly

13:14.461 --> 13:18.880
that you don't even know
when to be afraid.

13:20.550 --> 13:22.934
<i>It bothers you I'm not afraid.</i>

13:23.720 --> 13:28.223
Makes you feel impotent,
less powerful.

13:28.308 --> 13:32.977
- [whispers] You can't profile me.
- I don't have to.

13:33.063 --> 13:36.130
I already caught you.

13:38.201 --> 13:43.204
- I like you, Veronica.
- But you're still gonna cut my heart out.

13:45.158 --> 13:50.462
- Yes, I am.
- See what I mean?

13:50.580 --> 13:52.464
Fucking insane.

14:16.239 --> 14:20.492
- What's wrong?
- I just got a call

14:20.610 --> 14:23.695
about a handful of Calvin's
guys dead at the clubhouse.

14:25.332 --> 14:28.616
- Do you think Calvin did it?
- No, they're his guys.

14:28.702 --> 14:32.454
But I think the
Brotherhood is going to war.

14:32.539 --> 14:34.589
And I don't want to
have to worry about you

14:34.674 --> 14:36.174
while I'm dealing with Calvin.

14:36.293 --> 14:39.344
You're not safe here
at Brock's house anymore.

14:39.463 --> 14:43.598
I spoke to a friend in Dade County.
He's a retired cop.

14:43.683 --> 14:45.467
He's got a place in Turnberry Isle.

14:45.552 --> 14:48.937
You and Hank will be safe
there for the time being.

14:49.022 --> 14:51.139
- It won't be for long.
- You don't get it.

14:51.274 --> 14:54.642
No matter where we run, as
long as Calvin's breathing,

14:54.728 --> 14:58.480
- he's not gonna let me go.
- Yeah, it's me.

14:58.615 --> 15:00.899
I'm talking to your
fucking voicemail again.

15:00.984 --> 15:02.450
This is your last chance, Maggie.

15:02.536 --> 15:07.255
Tell me where the fuck you are
or I swear to God I will destroy...

15:09.075 --> 15:11.659
[sighs]
[humming]

15:11.795 --> 15:13.545
Call me back.

15:15.499 --> 15:17.332
[water running]

15:17.467 --> 15:19.884
Oh, shit.

15:22.172 --> 15:25.306
You really think I'll let this stand?

15:25.392 --> 15:28.843
You stupid bitch.
This will not fucking stand.

15:28.979 --> 15:32.397
I will fucking end you.
I will rip your fucking lungs out

15:32.516 --> 15:36.401
- and I will strangle you with them.
- Calvin?

15:40.490 --> 15:44.242
- Hello, Martin.
- What the hell are you doing?

15:46.780 --> 15:48.997
Jesus Christ.

15:55.372 --> 15:57.455
[grunts]

16:00.043 --> 16:02.677
Stupid gook motherfucker!

16:02.762 --> 16:05.930
[grunting]

16:06.049 --> 16:08.383
[screams]

16:08.518 --> 16:11.269
[panting]

16:12.272 --> 16:13.271
[spits]

16:13.390 --> 16:14.856
<i>[office chatter]</i>

16:14.941 --> 16:17.358
<i>[music playing]
Woman: Oh, my God.</i>

16:22.532 --> 16:26.414
<i>[distant siren wailing]</i>

16:43.253 --> 16:45.887
Senator Mitchum,
thank you for seeing me.

16:48.758 --> 16:52.310
I figure if it wasn't important,
you would have just called me.

16:54.097 --> 16:59.100
- So what is it?
- We had some complications.

17:00.437 --> 17:04.439
We can't afford any complications,
not with these people.

17:04.523 --> 17:08.276
Or we both wake up
strangled by our own tongues.

17:08.361 --> 17:11.913
I know that.
That's why I'm here.

17:11.998 --> 17:16.701
- You're having production problems?
- No, production is on schedule.

17:16.786 --> 17:21.172
I'm having... personnel issues.

17:37.524 --> 17:39.190
[knocks]

17:40.645 --> 17:43.728
[sighs]
Sheriff's Department!

17:45.448 --> 17:47.115
Hello!

17:49.369 --> 17:51.402
Check around back?

18:00.714 --> 18:02.714
It's open.

18:04.050 --> 18:08.002
<i>♪ Move over, sun ♪</i>

18:08.088 --> 18:10.555
<i>♪ And give me some sky... ♪</i>

18:10.674 --> 18:15.760
- We having company?
- Declan: Later.

18:15.845 --> 18:18.596
I'm not really dressed for it.

18:22.485 --> 18:25.186
And I could use a drink
if you're pouring.

18:26.856 --> 18:32.243
- What would you like?
- Whiskey, please.

18:32.362 --> 18:36.364
<i>♪ Make me some room ♪</i>

18:36.499 --> 18:39.083
<i>♪ You people up there ♪</i>

18:39.202 --> 18:42.370
<i>♪ On top of the world ♪</i>

18:42.505 --> 18:47.125
<i>♪ I'll meet you, I swear ♪</i>

18:47.210 --> 18:49.293
<i>♪ I'm staking my claim... ♪</i>

18:50.380 --> 18:52.213
[scoffs]
You're really gonna make me

18:52.298 --> 18:54.716
drink my last drink through a straw?

18:54.851 --> 18:57.885
We both know if I untie you,
you'll try to run.

18:58.021 --> 19:01.305
Then I'll have to rough you up
again to get you back on the table.

19:01.391 --> 19:04.025
And what would the neighbors think?

19:20.076 --> 19:25.496
- Nothing. I'll check upstairs.
- Okay.

19:45.485 --> 19:48.903
- So who's coming over?
- Just some friends.

19:50.156 --> 19:54.859
- You have a ritual.
- Yeah.

19:56.780 --> 20:00.114
- Upstairs is clear.
- She was here.

20:02.118 --> 20:06.537
Oh, shit. [sighs]
Well, she's not here now.

20:08.091 --> 20:10.885
I wonder if this place has a basement.

20:11.845 --> 20:15.096
Satan didn't tell you to kill me.
I just showed up.

20:15.181 --> 20:19.600
- I can't let you live.
- Maybe I could just join you

20:19.686 --> 20:22.470
and worship with you and your buddies?

20:22.555 --> 20:25.556
- No.
- Why not?

20:25.642 --> 20:27.358
Because Satan doesn't exist, remember?

20:27.477 --> 20:29.310
I'm pretty sure you said that.

20:30.780 --> 20:35.199
Nothing more annoying than a psychopath
who engages in Socratic debate.

20:48.331 --> 20:51.332
<i>[footsteps]
Shh.</i>

21:02.911 --> 21:06.717
[music]

21:33.343 --> 21:34.542
Now what?

21:36.546 --> 21:38.462
You okay? What's wrong?

21:47.440 --> 21:49.307
Hey.

21:56.482 --> 21:58.699
[sighs]

21:59.903 --> 22:05.289
- You look beautiful.
- Sorry, Kim. I'm not into girls.

22:05.408 --> 22:11.045
- My name is Lilith.
- No, it's not.

22:11.915 --> 22:17.218
You asked me how the sex was
when I met Declan.

22:19.589 --> 22:22.206
It was transcendent.

22:22.926 --> 22:25.259
<i>Like he was occupying my soul.</i>

22:25.345 --> 22:28.179
- It was rape.
- No.

22:28.264 --> 22:33.901
- You were a child.
- And he made me a woman.

22:41.611 --> 22:42.693
[grunts]

22:42.779 --> 22:44.946
- Hey, her car.
- What?

22:45.081 --> 22:47.081
Her car is in there.

22:48.418 --> 22:50.251
Give me a hand.

23:03.099 --> 23:05.716
<i>- This her car?
- Yeah.</i>

23:07.020 --> 23:09.937
- There's blood here.
- Shit.

23:32.495 --> 23:34.128
Hey, Hood.

23:34.213 --> 23:39.000
<i>- What?
- Diprivan. Brand name for Propofol.</i>

23:39.085 --> 23:40.885
<i>Same shit that killed Michael Jackson.</i>

23:41.004 --> 23:43.504
- What's it used for?
- General anesthesia.

23:43.589 --> 23:46.641
So what the fuck is
it doing in a garage?

23:48.845 --> 23:53.347
<i>[thuds, crashes] Brock?
Hey.</i>

23:53.348 --> 23:57.168
[music]

24:39.896 --> 24:40.861
<i>[rattling]</i>

24:40.947 --> 24:42.697
[grunts]

24:48.621 --> 24:51.619
[alarm chirps]
[lock clicks]

24:56.412 --> 24:58.913
[gasps, choking]

24:58.998 --> 25:03.918
Killers, rapists,
drug dealers...

25:04.053 --> 25:06.420
all walking the streets
because of you.

25:06.556 --> 25:08.422
No, it's Proctor.
It's Proctor.

25:08.508 --> 25:11.342
He threatened me.
I swear to God, he threat...

25:11.427 --> 25:16.097
You...
are the goddamn district attorney.

25:16.182 --> 25:18.182
[choking]

25:18.267 --> 25:22.987
He...
He threatened my family.

25:23.106 --> 25:25.439
I have three kids. Please.

25:25.575 --> 25:27.408
Please don't do this.
[sobs]

25:27.493 --> 25:29.493
[gasps]

25:30.947 --> 25:34.582
I want to know about everything
Proctor has his hands in.

25:35.952 --> 25:37.451
I only know what he wants me to know.

25:37.537 --> 25:39.453
- Are you lying to me?
- No.

25:39.539 --> 25:42.873
No, wait. Wait, wait, wait.
Wait.

25:42.959 --> 25:46.961
Last week...
last week he made my office

25:47.046 --> 25:49.880
seize all the tower records
from the old municipal airport.

25:49.966 --> 25:52.767
Why? Who's flying in?

25:54.604 --> 25:56.937
Emilio Loera.

25:58.608 --> 26:00.524
Loera?

26:00.643 --> 26:03.894
He's a major player in
the Colombian cartel.

26:03.980 --> 26:06.230
Proctor's selling to the cartel?

26:06.315 --> 26:08.032
I don't know.
I swear to God, I don't know.

26:08.151 --> 26:10.284
I'd tell you if I did.

26:14.874 --> 26:17.124
[gasping]

26:17.210 --> 26:19.743
- Go home.
- What?

26:19.829 --> 26:21.912
You just quit.

26:21.998 --> 26:26.798
Get your kids and get
the hell out of Banshee.

26:31.084 --> 26:34.831
[music]

26:36.596 --> 26:38.562
[coughing]

26:44.420 --> 26:47.021
[echoing] Hey, Hood.

26:49.692 --> 26:51.992
The dizziness comes in waves.

26:53.529 --> 26:55.830
<i>They must have drugged us.</i>

26:56.949 --> 26:59.950
[chains rattling]
[groans]

27:00.036 --> 27:01.952
You got any give on your cuffs?

27:04.090 --> 27:08.425
- No.
- Yeah, me neither.

27:08.544 --> 27:10.594
What is this?

27:11.764 --> 27:15.099
I don't know.
Some sort of basement.

27:18.271 --> 27:20.187
Of course.

27:21.140 --> 27:23.390
Did you get a look at him?

27:26.646 --> 27:28.229
He came to visit me the other night.

27:28.314 --> 27:30.814
- Who did?
- Bode.

27:34.537 --> 27:39.373
You saw him?
Why the fuck didn't you say anything?

27:39.458 --> 27:45.246
I don't know. Maybe I was...
spooked.

27:46.332 --> 27:47.581
<i>He knocked me out.</i>

27:47.667 --> 27:51.418
And when I came to, he
had a knife to my throat.

27:51.504 --> 27:55.256
He could have killed me right there,

27:55.391 --> 27:57.424
but he didn't.

27:59.011 --> 28:01.979
Said he wanted me to bear witness.

28:02.098 --> 28:04.899
- To what?
- I don't know.

28:06.402 --> 28:07.935
But I'm guessing we're
about to find out.

28:08.020 --> 28:12.239
So Dawson probably showed up
and got the same treatment.

28:12.325 --> 28:14.441
She might still be here.

28:14.577 --> 28:16.443
<i>Brock: If she's not already dead.</i>

28:16.579 --> 28:18.279
[grunting]

28:18.364 --> 28:21.282
Hey, I applaud your effort,
but you're not gonna break out

28:21.367 --> 28:23.367
of stainless steel cuffs, okay?

28:23.452 --> 28:26.337
You don't break the cuffs.
You work the links.

28:27.456 --> 28:29.540
If you're lucky, there's a defect.

28:29.625 --> 28:34.795
- Why don't you try yours again?
- All right.

28:39.185 --> 28:41.185
Ah, fuck.

28:41.304 --> 28:43.687
My right hand is a little loose.

28:43.806 --> 28:46.140
If I can just get
a little more leverage.

28:46.275 --> 28:48.359
They're solid. Stop it.

28:48.477 --> 28:51.478
Hood. Hood. Stop!
[Lucas grunting]

28:51.614 --> 28:54.365
<i>Hey, hey, look at me.
Give it up, all right?</i>

28:54.483 --> 28:56.483
We're not getting out of here.

29:06.879 --> 29:09.046
You know what sucks about this?

29:09.165 --> 29:11.715
I mean, besides the fact
that we're gonna die.

29:13.836 --> 29:17.537
I never got to be the
sheriff I wanted to be.

29:19.425 --> 29:23.060
I waited so long for this.
I waited for one sheriff to die.

29:23.179 --> 29:25.062
And then I had to wait
for you to burn out,

29:25.181 --> 29:28.182
which you did in such a big way.

29:28.317 --> 29:30.401
- No offense.
- None taken.

29:30.519 --> 29:33.437
I mean, okay, so I'm not
the most charming guy.

29:33.522 --> 29:36.774
I rub some people the wrong way
and, you know, I can't kiss ass.

29:36.859 --> 29:39.300
It's just not in my nature, you know?

29:39.335 --> 29:42.112
But I've never been afraid
to stand up to anybody

29:42.198 --> 29:44.865
who threatened the
well-being of my town.

29:46.335 --> 29:49.953
I wanted to be that guy, you know?

29:50.039 --> 29:53.497
The guy that made people feel safe.

29:56.178 --> 29:58.345
And I haven't done that.

30:07.390 --> 30:11.725
Hey.
Can I ask you something?

30:11.811 --> 30:14.061
- Be the last time.
- What?

30:15.231 --> 30:17.197
Who the fuck are you?

30:18.067 --> 30:22.152
<i>Really.
Who are you?</i>

30:22.238 --> 30:23.904
Look, I know you got
a lot of secrets, Hood.

30:24.040 --> 30:25.406
I'd be an idiot not to acknowledge that.

30:25.541 --> 30:26.824
No, we're not gonna
do that condemned men

30:26.909 --> 30:29.076
confess their sins shit, all right?

30:29.211 --> 30:31.662
- Yeah, I think that's exactly what we're gonna...
- No, we're not.

30:31.747 --> 30:33.747
Any minute now, that door is gonna open

30:33.833 --> 30:36.917
and something very bad
is gonna walk through it.

30:37.002 --> 30:39.386
Now, don't you want to meet
this with a clean conscience?

30:39.472 --> 30:41.588
- No, shut the fuck up.
- Come on, Hood, please listen.

30:41.674 --> 30:43.640
Then just answer the
fucking question for me!

30:43.759 --> 30:45.676
<i>- I said drop it, Brock!
- No, I'm not gonna drop it!</i>

30:45.761 --> 30:49.012
I want to know! Why are you here?
Why did you become a cop?

30:49.098 --> 30:53.434
I am not a cop!
I never was a fucking cop!

30:53.519 --> 30:55.269
<i>What are you...?</i>

30:55.354 --> 30:58.672
<i>- What does that... what does that mean?
- I'm not Lucas Hood!</i>

31:00.242 --> 31:01.275
<i>I saw him die.</i>

31:01.410 --> 31:05.412
I picked up his wallet and I became him.

31:05.498 --> 31:08.282
That's not even possible.
I don't... What are you...

31:08.417 --> 31:12.169
I'm a lie, Brock. I'm a fake.

31:12.288 --> 31:14.004
I was a thief.

31:14.123 --> 31:18.292
Not just a thief,
I'm a fucking infiltration specialist.

31:18.377 --> 31:21.712
<i>Diamonds, gold, art,
anything, I could get it.</i>

31:21.797 --> 31:25.132
The places no one could
get into, I got in.

31:27.470 --> 31:32.022
I had a good run,
but I got caught and I did 15 years.

31:32.141 --> 31:35.476
No, no. You're fucking with me.

31:35.611 --> 31:40.697
Come on.
You're an ex-con? No.

31:40.816 --> 31:43.367
<i>- That's right.
- No.</i>

31:49.542 --> 31:53.627
Who else knows about it?
Siobhan know?

31:54.997 --> 32:00.000
- In the end, yeah.
- Why would you do that? Why?

32:00.136 --> 32:03.170
Why would you come to this town
and pretend to be a cop?

32:03.305 --> 32:06.223
I don't know. I...

32:08.677 --> 32:10.677
When I got out...

32:12.181 --> 32:14.181
I had nothing.
[music]

32:15.684 --> 32:20.654
Whoever I was before... was gone.

32:23.242 --> 32:24.908
I was no one.

32:26.662 --> 32:29.830
<i>All I knew is I needed to be close...</i>

32:31.000 --> 32:33.534
to the one person who...

32:35.171 --> 32:37.171
who really knew me.

32:40.543 --> 32:44.795
- Carrie Hopewell?
- Ana.

32:46.382 --> 32:48.515
She was all I had.

32:50.019 --> 32:55.923
So when I got out, I tracked
her down and I came for her.

32:57.142 --> 33:00.727
But she had Gordon and
the kids and a life.

33:00.813 --> 33:02.362
<i>That's right.</i>

33:02.448 --> 33:05.032
Oh, my God.

33:05.117 --> 33:09.486
<i>I became... sheriff.</i>

33:14.877 --> 33:17.411
But you're not. You weren't.

33:17.546 --> 33:21.164
Well, I was getting up every day,
putting on the uniform.

33:23.052 --> 33:27.888
Eventually the... lie took over.

33:30.843 --> 33:35.429
I believed it.
I was... I was the sheriff.

33:40.236 --> 33:43.470
I was a cop and I liked it.

33:45.741 --> 33:47.941
I fucking loved it.

33:51.614 --> 33:53.580
Somehow it just...

33:56.035 --> 33:58.118
[sighs]
Somehow it just felt right.

33:58.254 --> 34:00.621
There's nothing fucking
right about what you did.

34:00.756 --> 34:03.257
It is the opposite of right.

34:03.342 --> 34:07.844
<i>You son of a bitch.
I believed you.</i>

34:07.963 --> 34:10.179
I trusted you. I followed you.

34:10.299 --> 34:13.467
- I killed for you.
- No.

34:13.552 --> 34:15.719
No, you killed for you.

34:16.804 --> 34:19.940
Not me.
I just showed you the way.

34:21.060 --> 34:24.444
A criminal. [laughs]

34:24.530 --> 34:29.783
That's rich.
I was deputy to a criminal.

34:31.620 --> 34:33.704
Oh, God.

34:35.407 --> 34:37.658
[laughing]

34:37.793 --> 34:39.793
Oh, God.

34:42.498 --> 34:44.414
Oh, God.

34:52.091 --> 34:54.474
It all makes sense now.

34:56.312 --> 34:58.428
All of it.

35:02.351 --> 35:04.484
I'm so stupid.

35:12.745 --> 35:14.328
[laughs]

35:22.087 --> 35:24.371
If you're not Lucas Hood...

35:25.374 --> 35:29.591
what's your name?
[door opens]

35:29.712 --> 35:31.595
Sheriff Lotus.

35:33.132 --> 35:35.932
It's good to see you again.

35:36.969 --> 35:38.435
And you.

35:38.554 --> 35:42.723
Dr. Quick tells me you're
friends with Agent Dawson.

35:42.808 --> 35:47.060
That's right.
And if you've hurt her in any way...

35:48.230 --> 35:50.397
I'm gonna fucking kill you.

35:52.901 --> 35:56.992
- You fellas are in for a treat tonight.
- Yeah?

35:57.027 --> 35:59.456
You gonna con another poor
girl into burning herself to a crisp?

35:59.575 --> 36:01.041
Gail was a true believer.

36:01.126 --> 36:04.461
No, she was a confused
and vulnerable young girl

36:04.580 --> 36:07.998
who you manipulated for
your own sick pleasure.

36:16.675 --> 36:18.258
[groans]

36:22.598 --> 36:26.066
It looks like you're going
to be my guests tonight.

36:26.151 --> 36:31.679
Thing is, we have a dress code,
so Dr. Quick is going to work

36:31.680 --> 36:36.493
his magic and make you look
a little more like family.

36:49.159 --> 36:53.731
[music]

37:02.971 --> 37:05.138
You bust into my office.

37:09.394 --> 37:11.478
You steal my camera.

37:14.533 --> 37:19.152
I gotta say,
I was hoping we would meet again.

37:20.456 --> 37:24.241
Gather round, everybody.
It's almost time to begin.

37:24.242 --> 37:28.242
[music]

37:38.891 --> 37:41.975
We have an unexpected offering tonight.

37:42.060 --> 37:45.061
<i>I think he will be pleased.</i>

37:46.265 --> 37:47.647
<i>Declan: Gloria Satanas.</i>

37:47.733 --> 37:50.317
<i>All: Satanas vobiscum.</i>

37:52.604 --> 37:56.740
<i>- Gloria Satanas.
- Satanas vobiscum.</i>

37:58.327 --> 37:59.526
<i>Gloria Satanas.</i>

37:59.661 --> 38:04.581
Don't worry, Sheriff.
This won't hurt a bit.

38:04.700 --> 38:08.001
<i>Well, maybe a little bit.</i>

38:10.038 --> 38:14.674
<i>Here we go. Gloria Satanas
et Belial et Spiritui maloso.</i>

38:14.760 --> 38:19.629
<i>All: Sicut erat in principo,
et nunc, et semper,</i>

38:19.715 --> 38:22.215
<i>et in saecula saeculorum.</i>

38:22.301 --> 38:25.406
Brock: No, no.
Stay the fuck away from me.

38:25.441 --> 38:28.104
Stay away!
Stay the fuck away from me!

38:30.025 --> 38:33.476
<i>Amen, evil from us deliver but</i>

38:33.562 --> 38:36.029
<i>temptation into not us lead and</i>

38:36.114 --> 38:39.199
us against trespass
